1 transactions and ensure pet owners, particularly those in rural
2 or underserved areas, can access medications at reasonable costs
3 while preserving high standards of veterinary care.
4 SECTION 2, Chapter 471, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
5 amended by adding a new section to be appropriately designated
6 and to read as follows:
7 ”§471- Requirements for written prescriptions. (a) A
8 veterinarian shall, upon the request of a client, provide a
9 written prescription for any medication prescribed for the
10 client’s animal patient without requiring the medication to be
11 dispensed directly by the veterinarian.
12 (b) A veterinarian shall give notice to a client of the
13 client's right to request a written prescription from the
14 veterinarian and the option to have it filled at a pharmacy of
15 the client's choice; provided that the notice may be given via
16 direct communication, posted signage, or digital communication.
17 (c) No veterinarian shall issue a written prescription
18 without the prior establishment of a veterinarian-client-patient
19 relationship, which shall require that a veterinarian has
20 conducted a timely examination of the animal patient or has made
21 medically appropriate visits to the premises where the animal
