1 (1) Responsible for the improper storage, potential
2 courrterfe it ijA2^jTiedlcabi^on substltut ion2 or dosa2e
3 errors that may be associated with dispensing from a
4 third-party pharmacy; or
5 (2) Liable for any adverse effects or lack of efficacy in
6 treatment due to externally sourced products.
7 (g) Any veterinarian who violates or fails to comply with
8 this section shall be deemed to have engaged in professional
9 misconduct and may be subject to disciplinary action by the
10 board pursuant to section 471-10, which may include fines, the
11 suspension or revocation of a license, or both.
12 (h) For the purposes of this section, "prescription" means
13 a written order for medication issued by a veterinarian licensed
14 in the State for the treatment of an animal patient."
15 SECTION 3. New statutory material is underscored.
16 SECTION 4. This Act shall take effect upon its approval.
